oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: American Trust Banking Company exterior view, circa 1930s
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Lamb, Herman
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black-and-white photograph of American Trust Banking Company located on Market Street at 8th Street in Chattanooga, Tennessee. The bank was in business from 192 to 1967. The building was covered in Italian marble and was demolished in 1968 to make way for the American National Bank building located at the intersection of Market and 8th Streets in downtown Chattanooga, Tennessee. The caption on the reverse of the image reads, "8th & Market 1930's."
